II. OS Options and Window Management1. Interface Controls
Options Menu:
Status: Enabled.
Includes: Settings, Full-screen Option, Search Bar.
Search Bar:
Status: Enabled.
Functionality: Must display immediate, relevant search results.
Clock Drawer:
Status: Enabled.


Sticky Notes:
Status: Enabled.
2. Application Window Features
App Window Navigation Bar:
Status: Enabled.
Layout: Home | New Tab | Back
App Window Tab Bar:
Status: Enabled.
Functionality: Allows users to switch between multiple application tabs without leaving the primary application window.
App Window Browser Bar:
Status: Enabled.
Functionality: Displays the current file/resource address or path.
App Window Screen Controls:
Functionality: Supports Close, Open, Minimize, and Maximize actions.
Fit: App windows must fit the screen dynamically, extending all the way to the taskbar area.
Desktop Window:
Functionality: Supports a full-screen option.
